HEADWORD: Colonization
<hw>Col`o*ni*za"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>colonisation</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act of colonizing, or the state
of being colonized; the formation of a colony or colonies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The wide continent of America invited <qex>colonization</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Bancroft.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Colonizationist</ent>⟦br⟧
